COPYRIGHT 2010 BLUE CROSS/BLUE SHIELD OF KANSAS CITY 

CALLED BY:  MedtrakDrugExtrSeq


DESCRIPTION:     Reads the ESIDrugFile.dat created in  ESIClmLand  job and puts the data into the claim  provider common record format and runs through primary key using Shared container ClmProvPkey
    

MODIFICATIONS:

Developer                Date                 Project/Altiris #      Change Description                                                                     Development Project      Code Reviewer          Date Reviewed       
------------------              --------------------     ------------------------      -----------------------------------------------------------------------                             --------------------------------       -------------------------------   ----------------------------       
Kaushik Kapoor       2018-01-22        5828                      Initial Programming                                                                      IntegrateDev2                 Kalyan Neelam          2018-02-26 

Sudhir Bomshetty    2018-04-13        5781 - HEDIS        Added the NTNL_PROV_ID                                                       IntegrateDev2                 Kalyan Neelam          2018-04-25

Peter Gichiri -  2019-10 -17   Added the stage Variables svSvcNtnlProvId  and svPcpNtnlProvId for SVC and PCP to populate NTNL_PROV_ID ,  
                                       For the PRSCRB mapped PROV.TAX_ID for the PROV_ID associated with the row, udated the logic for the PROV_ID 
                                      as per OptumRx requirements                                                                                                   IntegrateDev1


Rekha Radhakrishna 2019-11-04    6131- PBM Replacement modified  NTNL_PROV_ID logic modified for PRSCRB, SVC and PCP output links


Sharon Anderw           2019-11-04     OptumRX             modified all provider reference queries to provide the right keys for provider matching        Kalyan Neelam          2019-11-21
                                                                                      exluded  providers with NTNL_PROV_ID UNK and NA when the NTNL_PROV_ID was the field matched to
                                                                                      included new functions that check if the Prescriber ID and Prescriber NPI are valid DEA and NPI numbers
                                                                                      consolidated the Servicing and Prescriber look ups to the same hash files since they are all derived on same IDS Provider result sets.
                                                                                      constructed a new hierarchy of rules for determining the ServicingProviderID/NPI and PrescribingProviderID/NPI
